The paper discusses cybercrime and its mitigation, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the application of environmental criminology theories to cybercrime, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for defining cyberplaces, which could fall under the categories of computer networks and communications (cs.CC) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
